 own political beliefs and fantasies of power.) The student of classical history will find plenty in this book to enrich his own studies. The general reader will enjoy the vision of a classical world which differs radically from what he probably expects.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCivilization, Ancient. 0aCivilization, Classical. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aancient greece.  aancient history.  aancient rome.  aancient world.  aclassical world.  acontemporary historians.  acriticism.  ademocracy.  aessays.  aglobal influence.  aglobal literature.  agreece.  agreek history.  agreek society.  ahistorians.  ahistorical commentary.  ahistory and literature.  ahistory students.  ahistory.  ajuvenal.  aliterary criticism.  amodern historiography.  anonfiction.  aparthenon.  apoetry.  apower struggle.  aroman history.  aroman society.  asappho.  ascholars.  aworld history.  aworld literature.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025507440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093471940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520934719423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520934719/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY